549
00:35:24,800 --> 00:35:27,610

550
00:35:27,610 --> 00:35:31,180
And you should, or may,
also understand now

551
00:35:31,180 --> 00:35:34,390
why the sky is blue.

552
00:35:34,390 --> 00:35:37,210

553
00:35:37,210 --> 00:35:41,860
Here is the ground
and you are here.

554
00:35:41,860 --> 00:35:46,460
And here is, say, roughly the
top of the atmosphere.

555
00:35:46,460 --> 00:35:49,130
And the sunlight comes
in like this.

556
00:35:49,130 --> 00:35:54,750
Sun is infinitely far away, so
the sun comes in like this.

557
00:35:54,750 --> 00:35:58,290

558
00:35:58,290 --> 00:36:04,450
The atmosphere is full of very
small dust particles, smaller

559
00:36:04,450 --> 00:36:06,770
than a 10th of a micron.

560
00:36:06,770 --> 00:36:10,260
And even the density
fluctuations of the air

561
00:36:10,260 --> 00:36:13,740
molecules themselves are clearly
smaller than the 10th

562
00:36:13,740 --> 00:36:15,020
of a micron.

563
00:36:15,020 --> 00:36:18,520
And so you get ideal Rayleigh
scattering.

564
00:36:18,520 --> 00:36:21,890
So white light comes in,
you're standing here.

565
00:36:21,890 --> 00:36:25,040
But what is the light
that comes to you?

566
00:36:25,040 --> 00:36:26,930
Predominantly blue.

567
00:36:26,930 --> 00:36:29,170
So the sky is blue.

568
00:36:29,170 --> 00:36:32,600
The light that is scattered
here, comes to you is

569
00:36:32,600 --> 00:36:34,150
predominantly blue.

570
00:36:34,150 --> 00:36:36,400
So that's why the sky is blue.

571
00:36:36,400 --> 00:36:40,530
And so the reason is simply that
it is Rayleigh scattering

572
00:36:40,530 --> 00:36:43,895
of the dust particles
in the atmosphere.

573
00:36:43,895 --> 00:36:47,610

574
00:36:47,610 --> 00:36:53,970
If the sun is high in the sky,
the total amount of sunlight

575
00:36:53,970 --> 00:36:58,050
